A man who was trapped in a gold mine in Migori for two days has been rescued. Mr Joseph Otieno was trapped in Kanyasrega mines on Monday evening and was rescued on Wednesday evening. His three colleagues were however rescued on Monday. Mr Kepha Nyamita, the county executive member in charge of disaster said they had to use an excavator to remove soil from the mine. The victim was taken to hospital. The official asked miners in the region to be careful when prospecting for gold to avert disaster. 
 